This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new framework for domain adaptation using deep neural networks. It also involves learning a shared feature subspace and matching conditional distributions, which are common techniques in machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the proposed framework is evaluated on image classification tasks. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing a new framework for improving the performance of classifiers in related but not identical datasets. 

It could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the proposed framework involves matching conditional distributions, which is a common technique in natural language processing. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of deep neural networks in the proposed framework.
